reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars FIT THE DUO DRAWER WELL.
reviews.reviewText: These baskets allow for good air circulation during air frying. They are easy to clean. I wouldn't stack all three at once, though that would fit, but using two works very well. Little silicon separator clips are provided to extend the "leg" length. These baskets make a nice accessories to my Ninja dual drawer air fryer. I use them all the time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very snug fit if you use a silicone liner.
reviews.reviewText: Terrific product. I use it for fries, chicken cutlets, pork chops--just about everything I cook in my Ninja Dual Air Fryer. Keeps the food elevated so that hot air circulates evenly. Easy to clean. Just pop it in the dishwasher. Even after cooking pork chops slathered in BBQ sauce, these came out sparkling clean.Only one minor complaint. If you use silicone liners for your cook drawers (and I highly recommend you do), note that this rack fits in VERY snugly, making it a bit hard to get out when it's hot. I have to use tongs to get it out. As I said, though, a minor complaint.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It works with some minor issues
reviews.reviewText: I bought these for the air fryer hoping I could cook more in one pot each time - and I can. They do work great but there is some flaws. The racks do stack together but I found the heavier the food I'm cooking they did wobble/fall onto each other. It might be because the air fryer basket is bigger so there's more room for the baskets to shift. The other thing I noticed it that there actually isn't much space between each basket. So if you are cooking something that sticks up (e.g. chicken drummetts), they won't work. Chicken wings (wingetts) work well and bacon works well. FYI - bacon on the top basket will fly up during cooking. However, the cleaning up after is a bit awkward. Best to soak right away. I've done french toast sticks or bead and that works good. Overall, I do recommend these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good Baskets Bad Customer Service
reviews.reviewText: Everything is fine except it came with 8 rubber feet for 2 baskets. Unfortunately, i dont know if it's safe to use the rubber feet in my air fryer, are they toxic? Can they melt? No way to email of contact the seller of this item and Amazon has no idea. The baskets are shallow and the rubber feet elevate the baskets higher and will work much better and hold taller food.........if i can use them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A little small but work great
reviews.reviewText: I have the Ninja DZ401 and apparently no one makes parts that fit it - even Ninja doesn't have replacement crisper plates for it and the finish comes off of them. That's where these things come in handy. We use silicone paper inserts and 1 rack in each drawer every time we use it now. This helps with the cooking somewhat, at least crisping the bottom without having to flip it. I don't believe it cooks it more evenly or anything. Like them so much we just ordered another 6. Easiest way to clean them is just throw 'em in the dishwasher.
